  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
   The sign for
   <span style="font-weight: 400">
    "room" is the same as the sign 
	for "box." Use flat hands to show the sides and then bent hands to show the 
	front and back of the room or box.
    <br/>
    <br/>
    ROOM (or "box" -- depending on context)
   </span>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <iframe allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ByET2PW3OrQ?rel=0" width="560">
    </iframe>
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
     <span style="font-weight: 400">
      <img border="0" height="480" src="/images/room-box.gif" width="480"/>
     </span>
     <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
      <span style="font-weight: 400">
       <br/>
       <br/>
       <img border="0" height="300" src="/images/room-b1.jpg" width="326"/>
       <img border="0" height="300" src="/images/room-b2.jpg" width="326"/>
       <br/>
       <br/>
       Note: The sign ROOM is based on the concept of "a box." Thus this sign can 
	be interpreted as either "room" or "box" depending on context to make your 
	meaning clear.
       <br/>
      </span>
      <span style="font-weight: 400">
       <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
      </span>
      <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
       <span style="font-weight: 400">
        <br/>
